In a message dated 12/29/2002 2:46:43 PM Pacific Standard Time, 
conradk(-at-)mac.com writes:
> This is my first experience using nyloc nuts - the last time I worked with 
> suspension components they only had castelated nuts.

Hi Conrad,
Get rid of the nyloc nuts!  Castalated nuts are the only way to do tie rods 
ends properly.  Otherwise as you found out the threaded shaft of the rod end 
spins and there is no way to ensure that the tightening of the nyloc nut will 
not back off.
